Class AbstractGameObject

java.lang.Object
  AbstractGameObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
GameObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractMovable, Block, Magnet
public abstract class AbstractGameObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements GameObject

This class is the abstract class that is used as the super class for all GameObjects. Though no methods in this class are specifically abstract, some subclasses may have to, but not necessarily will override methods in this class. This method overrides all inherited methods from GameObject with the default code that will be used by most if not all instances and subclasses of GameObjects. Subclasses of this class do not have mutator methods X and Y values, as they will never be moved. In order for a GameObject to be movable, they must either implement the Movable interface, of be subclasses of AbstractMovable.

removeSelfFromWorld

public void removeSelfFromWorld()
Description copied from interface: GameObject
Removes the GameObject from the World Object that it's value is currently enclosed within. Also sets the value for the field that stores the current value for the World Object to null. If the GameObject is not in a World when this method is called, it will perform no action. Implementing classes must override this method.
